naturalness 3.56 4.60 3.67 + 0.07 +0.07 + 0.19 +0.19 + 0.05 +0.05 Table 9: Per-rater means and pairwise rater-rater Spearman ρ \\rho across the 209-session pool. R1 , R2 , R3 are anonymous rater identifiers. Rater-mean spread on the same dimension reaches 1.11 points on speech_clarity (R1 3.74 vs R3 4.85) and 1.12 points on audio_clarity (R1 3.66 vs R2 4.78). This variance underlies the observation in Section 4.4 that the LALM’s consistent ratings land closer to the across-rater mean than any single rater’s ratings do to another rater’s on many dimensions. B.5 Per-stratum breakdown Table 10 summarises LALM-vs-human agreement per stratum for the two most illustrative dimensions: audio_clarity , where humans show real rank-discrimination (Section 4.1 ), and accent_dialect_handling , which sits near the top of the scale (Section 4.5 ). The full 14-stratum × \\times 8-dimension table is available in h2_per_config_per_dim.csv . audio_clarity accent_dialect_handling Stratum n ρ L ​ H ¯ \\rho_{L\\bar{H}} L%1 ρ L ​ H ¯ \\rho_{L\\bar{H}} L%1 clean-american-1 10 + 0.09 +0.09 100 — 100 clean-american-2 38 + 0.21 +0.21 95 − 0.14 -0.14 95 clean-indian 10 − 0.54 -0.54 90 + 0.60 +0.60 90 clean-british 10 − 0.06 -0.06 90 − 0.11 -0.11 100 clean-french 10 − 0.32 -0.32 90 + 0.68 +0.68 90 codec-american-1 9 — 100 — 100 codec-american-2 10 − 0.07 -0.07 100 — 100 codec-indian 10 − 0.11 -0.11 90 − 0.41 -0.41 90 codec-indian-2 10 − 0.27 -0.27 80 − 0.10 -0.10 80 codec-british 10 + 0.07 +0.07 90 — 100 codec-french 10 + 0.51 +0.51 100 + 0.78 +0.78 100 codec-italian 10 + 0.04 +0.04 100 − 0.27 -0.27 100 adversarial 57 + 0.56 +0.56 79 − 0.18 -0.18 88 Table 10: Per-stratum LALM-vs-human agreement on two representative dimensions. Here ρ L ​ H ¯ \\rho_{L\\bar{H}} is the Spearman correlation between the LALM and the mean human rating (distinct from ρ L ​ H \\rho_{LH} in Table 5 , which averages the three LALM-vs-individual -rater correlations); per-stratum n n is too small to compute the three-pair